-- South Africa Gold Shares Fall Most Since September, Led Down by AngloGold
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2010-12-17T07:06:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/south-africa-gold-shares-fall-most-since-september-led-down-by-anglogold.html
The FTSE/JSE Africa Gold Mining
Index fell as much as 4.4 percent to 2,708.41 and traded 4.3
percent down as of 9:04 a.m. Johannesburg time, heading for its
biggest fall since September.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd., Gold Fields Ltd. and Harmony Gold
Mining Co. are the biggest stocks on the index.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  